CONTINUOUS COMPOUNDING
Section::::Continuous compounding.
As n, the number of compounding periods per year, increases without limit, the case is known as continuous compounding, in which case the effective annual rate approaches an upper limit of , where  is a mathematical constant that is the base of the natural logarithm.
