FORCE OF INTEREST
Section::::Force of interest.
As the number of compounding periods formula_13 reaches infinity in continuous compounding, the continuous compound interest is referred to as the force of interest formula_14.
In mathematics, the accumulation functions are often expressed in terms of e, the base of the natural logarithm. This facilitates the use of calculus to manipulate interest formulae.
